-- UK property company Hammerson placing 71 mln new shares
-- By Karolin Schaps
-- Thu Sep 25, 2014 03:37AM EDT
-- None



LONDON, Sept 25 (Reuters) - British property firm Hammerson <HMSO.L> is selling up to 71.3 million new shares to fund the purchase of its joint venture partner's stake in a shopping centre in Leicester, central England, and a planned expansion in outlet fashion centres.

Hammerson is proposing to place the shares, which will represent around 10 percent of the company's current share capital, with investment institutions via an accelerated bookbuild. Its shares were trading down 2.6 percent at 569 pence by 0827 GMT.